                    "node": {
                        "created_at": "1770776651",
                        "id": "18110326048672575",
                        "text": "Golden Gai is one of the most recommended nightlife spots in Tokyo \u2014 and it can be fun.\nBut it\u2019s also crowded, loud, and doesn\u2019t always feel very local.\n\nThis is why I recommend Nakano instead.\n\nYou still get the character people are looking for \u2014 but with local bars, record shops, retro arcades, and a neighborhood vibe that feels lived-in rather than performative.\n\nThis is how I plan Tokyo nights:\nby choosing places where locals actually spend time, not just what shows up on every list.\n\nSave this for your Tokyo trip \ud83c\uddef\ud83c\uddf5\nComment SWAP and I\u2019ll DM you my neighborhood swap list with more hidden spots.\nFollow @laurahtravel for calm, intentional Japan planning.\n\n#TokyoTravel\n#JapanPlanning\n#HiddenTokyo\n#TokyoNights\n#japantraveltips"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
